    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="277"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adam</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Manchester, Mass.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-07-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 21, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note to Mr. Tower, No.
                    719, of the 2d instant, respecting the number of vessels employed on patrol
                    duties in Bering Sea during the present season, I have the honor to inform you,
                    in compliance with an instruction from the Marquis of Salisbury, that Her
                    Majesty’s Government have decided to send a third vessel, Her Majesty’s ship <hi
                        rend="italic">Amphion</hi>, to Bering Sea, besides Her Majesty’s ships <hi
                        rend="italic">Wild Swan</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Pheasant.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">C. F. Frederick Adam.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
